external_knowledge:
- Contributions involving bug fixes are represented by pull requests with the label 'bug';
- At least a few contributions means the number of such contributions must be greater than or equal to one;
- Contributors are users who have created pull requests.

- "top contributors" refers to users who have submitted the highest number of pull requests;
- "pull requests" are requests to make changes or modifications to a repository in a collaborative coding environment;
- "most active" in this context means the users who have submitted the most pull requests.

sql:
SELECT i.title, pr.status
FROM issues i
JOIN pull_requests pr ON i.issue_id = pr.issue_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'gardeners' refers to users who have created pull requests;
- 'seeds of discussion' are the comments made by users on their own pull requests, indicating their engagement;
- 'garden beds' symbolize pull requests, which are like the spaces where these discussions take place.

sql:
SELECT base_repo_id, COUNT(*) AS pull_request_count
FROM pull_requests
GROUP BY base_repo_id;

SELECT review_status
FROM pull_request_reviews
WHERE review_status = 'approved';

SELECT AVG(comments_count) AS Average_Comments
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(comment_id) AS comments_count
  FROM pull_request_comments
  GROUP BY pull_request_id
) AS CommentCount;

SELECT strftime('%Y-%m', created_at) AS Month, COUNT(pull_request_id) AS NewlyCreatedPullRequests
FROM pull_requests
GROUP BY strftime('%Y-%m', created_at);

